        </li>
              <li>
          <div><div>  <a href="/blog/essay/palestinian-novelist-sahar-khalifeh-exploring-nakba-and-gender-politics-palestine-fakhri" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/medium_thumbnail/public/Saleh-anchor.jpg?itok=_hBuELRw" width="250" height="175" alt="A collage of the books discussed below" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-medium-thumbnail" />

</a>

</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><p class="field-content"><a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/essay/palestinian-novelist-sahar-khalifeh-exploring-nakba-and-gender-politics-palestine-fakhri">Palestinian Novelist Sahar Khalifeh: Exploring the Nakba and Gender…</a>
</p></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-author"><span class="views-label views-label-field-author field-name-field-blogauthor">By</span><span class="field-content field-name-field-blogauthor"><a href="/author/fakhri-saleh" hreflang="en">Fakhri Saleh</a>
</span></div>
        </li>
          </ul>
